item.title: I know nothing about everything, but this seems like a great move.
item.description: New York Mayor Zohran Mamdani has appointed a former prisoner to run jails. 64-year-old Stanley Richards has been appointed as New York City’s commissioner of the department of correction. He will be the first person who has served time to lead the department. Richards spent two and a half years in Rikers Island - the city’s largest jail - and another four and a half years in state prison for robbery in the late 1980s. He was released from prison in 1991. Since then he has worked helping people prepare for their release from prison and re-entry into society. Mamdani said Richards’ appointment is “a testament to the thought and leadership he will bring to every member of Correction staff and incarcerated New Yorkers underneath his purview”. Richards said: “My experience and journey is a testament that when we provide support, when we centre our collective work to hope instead of fear, when we see the best in all of us instead of judging people in the worst thing we ever done, when we see our commonality [more] than our difference, we can achieve the unimaginable.” Jails are a thorny political issue for Mamdani. Prior to his election, the democratic socialist called for “no new jails”. Now in power, he must oversee the closing of Rikers Island and its replacement with four new prisons.

item.title: Update on Pongo and Galadriel to draw attention to baby girl Kay Rose
item.description:
I came by the humane society today to drop off some food that some wonderful imgurian’s gifted us and I got to see Pongo! He’s almost three pounds and has NO symptoms of the toxoplasmosis that took his sister Paisley, so he’s gonna be fixed and put up for adoption next week! He’s right next to Magnolia who is SO beautiful. I wanted to take her home but they said she’s ready to be spayed and put up for adoption so she doesn’t need a foster
Baby girl Galadriel is living her best life in her forever home! Jess adopted her and her husband “didn’t want a cat” but he obviously loves her very much!
Jess says she sleeps on her chest and chews her chin in the morning when it’s time to wake up haha
Ok but all of this is to draw attention to Kay Rose. She is the longest resident of the humane society. She has been here OVER A YEAR. They got her as a kitten and she has been overlooked time and time again
The CEO of the humane society asked me to post her. He has literally never once asked me for a favor for one of his kittens so I know he’s desperate and of course I said I would tell her story. Spencer was more than happy to tell us all about her.
As Spencer said, she has some tummy issues which is a major reason why she has been overlooked for over a year. But she’s still a kitten, not even two years old
They found her huddling in their food kitchen, King’s Kitchen, so they named her KK but have recently renamed her Kay Rose. She knew a safe space when she found it, and she has been taken care of by these amazing humans for over 365 days.
Kay Rose has inflammatory bowel disease and a stomach ulcer which has required a LOT of meds. BUT they have FINALLY found a food that alleviates the symptoms.
She has started to shut down, having been in the humane society for so long. I didn’t get a video of it, but when I reached in to pet her, she immediately recoiled but then very carefully, and very lovingly, put her face in my hand. Broke my heart. She has a lot of love to give but she’s so shy and scared from her time in the cage.
I’m not going to lie, Kay Rose is going to require a very special home. She’s not good with other cats and has specific dietary needs. She’s not a cat for the faint of heart.
But everyone at the humane society has come to love her very much. And I fell in love with her immediately. And, as Spencer said in the video, we are willing to drive her ANYWHERE in the continental United States to find her a home.
Less than a month ago, Spencer drove baby girl Arwen from Alabama to Iowa to get to her forever home! We are not kidding, we will drive Kay Rose ANYWHERE, free of charge!!
Anyone who adopts her will get the adoption fee paid for, AND a front-door delivery, AND one year worth of food!
I absolutely fell in love with her when I was there. I had no idea they have a cat who has been there for over a year. If you listened hard enough, she was purring.
This baby girl deserves a home. Leaving her in that cage absolutely broke my heart. If you aren’t interested in adopting her, please give an updoot to spread the word on her. Let’s find Kay Rose a home!! I have gotten a few people who have offered to donate to finding a home for Kay Rose. If the mood strikes you, here it is! https://gofund.me/81e1d6f16
